# fusion-box wine patch 0008
# Raise sibling overlay wl_subsurfaces above a freshly-(re)anchored client
# wl_subsurface (DXVK/Vulkan swapchain), restoring static UI visibility.
#
# Bug - Object Browser, Comment menu, and nav toolbar disappear after sketch
# entry/exit, viewport scroll, viewport-tool dialogs (CREATE menu items),
# component activate, browser undock, and similar actions; never reappear
# without restarting Fusion. User-reported "they come back briefly at
# shutdown" was the load-bearing clue: the widgets are NOT destroyed - they
# exist, render, and commit buffers throughout the run. Verified
# 2026-06-10 by:
#   - 30-second-wait-at-main-UI controlled reproducer: 0 destroys during
#     the wait; widget HWNDs (Browser, Comments, navbar) continue
#     committing buffers via patch 0006's vsub path. Stable identifier
#     logging (class, text, rect) at WAYLAND_DestroyWindow confirmed no
#     Fusion-UI destroys at sketch transition - only Qt6 internal
#     tooltip/popup-save-bits churn.
#   - Initial misdiagnosis was "destroy-without-recreate" - falsified by
#     timing analysis (the destroys we attributed to sketch-exit were
#     actually shutdown destroys at 99% of run; main HWND survived to
#     line 25244 while "destroyed" children were also at 99% i.e.
#     simultaneous shutdown cascade).
#
# Root cause - z-order, not lifecycle:
#
# When Qt6 reanchors a child window's DXVK/Vulkan swapchain to a different
# toplevel parent (sketch mode swaps the viewport host, scroll out/in
# remaps client coords, etc.), wine's wayland_client_surface_attach takes
# the toplevel-change branch (wayland_surface.c:1444):
#
#   1. wl_subsurface_destroy(client->wl_subsurface)
#   2. client->wl_subsurface = wl_subcompositor_get_subsurface(
#                                  client->wl_surface, surface->wl_surface)
#
# Per Wayland spec (wl_subcompositor.get_subsurface): the newly-created
# subsurface is placed at the TOP of the parent surface's substack. Any
# pre-existing sibling subsurfaces - patch 0006's virtual-buffer subsurface
# for the nav toolbar, Qt6 docked panels like Object Browser and Comment
# menu (SUBSURFACE role parented to main's wl_surface) - get pushed below
# the freshly-anchored DXVK swapchain. The viewport swapchain rect
# (typically 2554x1195 at offset 3,120) covers all three UI elements'
# screen positions, so they vanish from view.
#
# Same family of bug as patch 0002 (which removed wl_subsurface_place_above
# from the per-frame reconfigure_* paths to stop overlays being shoved down
# the stack on every focus event). Patch 0002 stopped the per-frame thrash
# but didn't address the per-event re-anchor: every (re)attach call still
# resets the new subsurface to TOP.
#
# Diagnostic evidence in the validation run (2026-06-10):
#   - 12 `[fusion-box patch 0008] client (re)anchor` events in a typical
#     session (initial widget setup + sketch-cycle reanchors)
#   - 10 with raised=0 (early lifecycle, no overlays exist yet)
#   - 2 with raised=5 (sketch entry + exit), corresponding exactly to the
#     5 user-visible static UI elements (navbar vsub + Browser + Comments +
#     2 ribbon-area widgets) being lifted back above the swapchain
#   - User confirmation: "obj browser, comment, and navbar stayed!"
#
# Fix - one helper + one call:
#
# 1. raise_overlay_siblings_above_client (window.c) - given the
#    wl_surface of a just-anchored client subsurface plus its toplevel
#    HWND, walk the wayland_win_data rb tree (the same tree patch 0003's
#    detach_client_subsurfaces_for_toplevel walks) and for each entry
#    whose wayland_surface->toplevel_hwnd matches and which has its own
#    wl_subsurface (excluding the client surface itself), call
#    wl_subsurface_place_above(sibling_sub, client_wl_surface). Single
#    pass; the static UI elements don't visually overlap each other
#    (navbar bottom-center, Browser right side, Comments top-right), so
#    no need to chain place_above sibling-to-sibling - each just needs to
#    be above the client. Header guard: bail if !toplevel || !surface.
#
# 2. Call site in wayland_client_surface_attach (wayland_surface.c) -
#    inserted at the end of the toplevel-change branch, after the new
#    wl_subsurface is created, set_desync'd, and client->toplevel is
#    updated. Two TRACE calls added: one announcing the re-anchor (logs
#    old/new toplevel HWNDs), one inside the helper logging the count of
#    siblings raised.
#
# Coverage (validated against Fusion 360 v2703.1.11 on KDE Plasma 6
# Wayland with NVIDIA Open 610.43.02):
#   - Sketch entry/exit: nav toolbar, Browser, Comments stay visible
#   - Viewport scroll out/in: same
#   - Browser undock (drag out of dock): works, slightly stuttery
#   - CREATE menu items (e.g. Extrude): perfect
#   - Component activate/deactivate: looks good
#
# Out of scope for this patch (separate bugs):
#   - Bottom timeline disappears on window resize. The timeline is a
#     selfroot Qt683QWindowToolSaveBits (TOPLEVEL/POPUP role, NOT a
#     subsurface of main), so it's not a sibling in main's substack and
#     this patch doesn't reach it. Needs its own fix.
#   - Workspace switch (Design <-> Render <-> Drawing dropdown) - looks
#     promising but exhibits other rendering issues; deferred.
#   - Section analysis - deferred.
#
# Drive-by: format-string cast in patch 0006's vsub CREATED trace
# (window.c). Wine's LONG typedefs to int on x86_64 Linux but the format
# string used %ld; previously a silent warning, became an error in our
# build environment when a new TRACE elsewhere triggered the diagnostic
# bundle. Belongs in patch 0006 but folded here for the audit trail of
# when it was caught.
#
# Status: verified working 2026-06-10. Trace mechanism matches theory.
# User confirmed all three target UI elements (navbar, Browser, Comments)
# stay visible across all reproducible triggers.
#
# Upstream: candidate for wine-devel. The patch is small (~50 lines), the
# Wayland-spec reasoning is precise, and the rb-tree walk pattern mirrors
# patch 0003's already-merged-style helper. The argument needs framing
# carefully: this is a band-aid for Qt6/Win32 application code that
# repeatedly reattaches client surfaces to the same logical parent; the
# "correct" fix is for the application not to do that, but Qt does and
# the resulting z-order regression is severe for any DXVK-backed app
# with overlay UI (CAD, IDE, graphics tools, etc).
#
# Apply from the wine source root: `patch -p1 < this-file`. Depends on
# patches 0001-0007 (line offsets assume all are applied).
#
# Author: fusion-box (claude-code session, with Barrett Otte)
#
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/waylanddrv.h
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/waylanddrv.h
@@ -432,6 +432,14 @@
  * leaving child subsurfaces orphaned when their parent wl_surface dies. */
 void detach_client_subsurfaces_for_toplevel(HWND toplevel);

+/* fusion-box patch 0008: after a client wl_subsurface is (re)anchored to a
+ * toplevel (which places it at TOP of the parent's substack per Wayland
+ * spec), walk the wayland_win_data rb tree and place_above each sibling
+ * overlay subsurface to lift them back atop the freshly-anchored client.
+ * Fixes static UI burial under DXVK swapchains at Fusion 360 sketch
+ * entry/exit. */
+void raise_overlay_siblings_above_client(struct wl_surface *client_wl_surface, HWND toplevel);
+
 struct wayland_client_surface *get_client_surface(HWND hwnd);
 void set_client_surface(HWND hwnd, struct wayland_client_surface *client);
 BOOL set_window_surface_contents(HWND hwnd, struct wayland_shm_buffer *shm_buffer, HRGN damage_region);
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/window.c
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/window.c
@@ -198,6 +198,49 @@
 }

 /***********************************************************************
+ *           raise_overlay_siblings_above_client  (patch 0008)
+ *
+ * After a DXVK/Vulkan client wl_subsurface is (re)anchored to a toplevel via
+ * wl_subcompositor_get_subsurface (in wayland_client_surface_attach), the
+ * newly-created subsurface lands at the TOP of the parent's substack per
+ * Wayland spec. For Fusion 360 this happens at sketch entry/exit when Qt6
+ * reanchors the viewport's DXVK swapchain - the swapchain ends up above the
+ * static overlay UI (navbar vsub from patch 0006, Object Browser, Comment
+ * menu, etc.). Same family as patch 0002's fix for the reconfigure_* paths,
+ * but the (re)attach path was missed.
+ *
+ * Walk the wayland_win_data rb tree finding sibling wl_subsurfaces of the
+ * same toplevel (excluding the client_surface itself) and call
+ * wl_subsurface_place_above(sibling, client_wl_surface) on each. The
+ * static UI elements don't visually overlap, so we don't need to chain
+ * place_above sibling-to-sibling - each just needs to be above the client.
+ */
+void raise_overlay_siblings_above_client(struct wl_surface *client_wl_surface, HWND toplevel)
+{
+    struct wayland_win_data *entry;
+    int raised = 0;
+
+    if (!toplevel || !client_wl_surface) return;
+
+    pthread_once(&win_data_mutex_once, win_data_mutex_init);
+    pthread_mutex_lock(&win_data_mutex);
+    RB_FOR_EACH_ENTRY(entry, &win_data_rb, struct wayland_win_data, entry)
+    {
+        struct wayland_surface *s = entry->wayland_surface;
+        if (!s) continue;
+        if (!s->wl_subsurface) continue;
+        if (s->wl_surface == client_wl_surface) continue;
+        if (s->toplevel_hwnd != toplevel) continue;
+        wl_subsurface_place_above(s->wl_subsurface, client_wl_surface);
+        raised++;
+    }
+    pthread_mutex_unlock(&win_data_mutex);
+
+    TRACE("[fusion-box patch 0008] raised=%d overlay siblings above re-anchored client on toplevel=%p\n",
+          raised, toplevel);
+}
+
